n of consumption as an expression of perfection. As meaningful as any prospective bride might wish, the lavish wedding emerges here as a lens that at once reveals, magnifies, and reveres some of the dearest wishes and darkest impulses at the heart of our culture.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aConsumer behavior. 0aWeddings in popular culture. 0aWeddings. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  aamerican culture.  abeauty.  abridal industry.  abridal.  acinderella.  aconsumer culture.  aconsumption.  acultural rituals.  adiamond rings.  adiscussion books.  ahistorical perspective.  ahistorical.  alavish weddings.  alove and marriage.  alove.  amarriage.  amorality and virtue.  anonfiction.  aprincesses.  apsychological framework.  arelationships.  aromance.  aromantic love.  asocial relationships.  awedding culture.  awedding gowns.  awedding stereotypes.  awedding traditions.  aweddings.  awhite weddings.1 aPleck, Elizabeth, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052093750540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520937505423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520937505/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles